Learn Your Structures Arcana Stones You and your opponent each have three of these immobile crystals on the playing field. Shatter all of your enemy's Arcana Stones to claim victory. Gates Minions will appear in front of your currently selected gate. Returning minions to a gate area will restore their HP. Minions can still be summoned from a destroyed gate, but they will be unable to exit the gate area. Conversely, minions outside a destroyed gate will be unable to enter. Search Eye This structure reveals your opponent's minions. If the Search Eye is destroyed, you will only be able to see enemy units that are near your own minions. Shield This structure adds defensive strength to Arcana Stones. Destroy the enemy Shield and your opponent's Arcana Stones will be more easily shattered. Structural Regeneration All structures except for Arcana Stones can only be temporarily destroyed. Their various functions will reactivate at full strength after a certain amount of time has passed. ※Positioning your minions near a destroyed structure will hasten 　the reactivation process. Play to Your Minions' Strengths Each variety of minion is capable of inflicting greater damage against certain structures. Learn each unit's strengths, and pick the right minion for the job! Turn the Tide with Special Actions These conditions must be met before a special action can be used: ・Four minions of the same variety are gathered in an action party ・Each minion in the action party has full action points (Action points accumulate over time) To perform a special action, select an individual minion from the action party, and press the Execute Action button on the minion hotbar. Mastering Traps Some minions will place traps with their special actions. A trap will become armed ten seconds after it has been placed, and it can then be triggered by pressing the Trigger Trap button on the minion hotbar. ※Only one trap can be placed at a time. You may challenge previously completed main scenario dungeons of level 71 and above with a party of NPC avatars. Avatars will gain EXP and level up in accordance with their duty participation. ※When using Trust, coffers found in the duty will contain fewer items. In addition, some enemies will no longer drop rewards.
The glamour system will be unlocked for NPC avatars who have attained level 80. Use the Glamour icons or subcommand from the party selection window to adjust character appearances.
It should be noted that certain avatars may not be permitted to accompany you into some instanced dungeons.

You may challenge a dungeon via two different methods: by calling upon the support of trusty NPCs, or by forming a party with other players. Player parties may be preformed or assigned via the Duty Finder. No matter what method you choose, the duty that awaits will offer comparable difficulty and experience. ※When challenging a duty with NPCs, coffers will contain fewer items. In addition, some enemies will no longer drop rewards.

By choosing Duty Support under Duty in the main menu, or by accessing the entrance of any applicable duty, you can summon a team of NPC allies to assist you. NPC parties will be automatically balanced to suit your current class or job. Once you have made your preparations, select Register for Duty, and ready yourself for battle!

Once you have registered and your duty is available, a prompt window indicated by a notification sound will appear. Begin duty by selecting Commence. ※Please note that if you do not commence duty within the time limit, your registration will be automatically withdrawn, and you must start the process over.

Over the course of your adventures, the number of duties available to you will gradually increase. Should you encounter a duty for which NPC support is not available, access the Duty Finder to team up with other players instead. You may also rechallenge previously cleared duties by using either the Duty Finder or Duty Support, both accessible via Duty in the main menu.

When challenging main scenario duties of level 71 and above, you may choose your favorite support NPCs with which to form a party. Click on a member of your current party to see all members available for selection.

The Duty Finder allows you to challenge dungeons and other duties with a party of other players. You may access it via Duty in the main menu, or by choosing the appropriate option at the entrance of any duty.

Enter dungeons and other duties via the Duty Finder by choosing your desired duty, then selecting Join. You will then be automatically matched with compatible players destined for the same duty. ※You may register for up to five duties at one time. ※Duties marked by a lock symbol require certain conditions to be met before becoming accessible.
When you register for a duty, it will appear along with an icon in your duty list. You may check duty status, including matching progress and approximate waiting times, by selecting this entry.

Once you have been successfully matched with other players, a prompt window indicated by a notification sound will appear. Begin duty by selecting Commence. ※Please note that if you do not commence duty within the time limit, your registration will be automatically withdrawn, and you must start the process over.

Over the course of your adventures, the number of duties available to you will gradually increase. Many duties can be cleared via both the Duty Finder and Duty Support systems, so it's worth familiarizing yourself with both. You may also rechallenge previously cleared dungeons by accessing Duty Finder or Duty Support via Duty in the main menu.

The following conditions must be met to use the Duty Recorder: 　1. Recorder is enabled. 　2. Current duty is available for recording. 　3. Parties meet minimum size requirements. 　4. Record ready check has been executed. 1. Recorder settings are enabled Recorder settings can be adjusted under Duty Recorder in the main menu. 2. Current duty is available for recording Not all duties are available for recording. Recordable duties are marked with a special icon. 3. Parties meet minimum size requirements Duties undertaken by undersized parties cannot be recorded. ※This includes parties formed via the Duty Finder. ※Duties with the unrestricted party setting enabled cannot be recorded, even if minimum party size requirements are met. 4. Record ready check has been executed Approval from all party members is required before recording can begin. ※Record ready checks must be performed within 5 minutes of commencing a duty. Only 3 records may be saved at once. Oldest records will be overwritten. ※Up to 2 records can be protected at once.

The following conditions must be met to view duty records: 　1. You are in an inn room. 　2. Recorded duty is from the most recent game version. 1. You are in an inn room Duty playback is only available in inn rooms. 2. Recorded duty is from the most recent game version This includes both major updates and minor hotfixes. Recordings will become inaccessible after applying the newest data patch.
